      "content": "I see. So if there's a consensus that it's a critical threat, then wouldn't the \"accelerationist\" view—the one that says we should just keep moving as fast as possible—be seen as fundamentally irresponsible or even dangerous? Like, if the risk is real, isn't any delay in regulation basically just gambling with our survival?",
